page.title: 07BILLERICAY NW Transport_Cars
page.content: {Cars and Car Parks. Most people have private cars. In this part of Billericay there are two {service stations.}Both had petrol pumps and they can also supply parts for modern cars. One garage is opposite the station and the other is situated in the middle of the industrail estate. Both do M.O.T. testing. There are two{car parks}for people who use the railway. One of the car parks could only be entered by season ticket holders. The other one costs money to enter. By the side of every factory unit there is a small private car park. Lake Meadows has one main car park and several smaller ones.
